			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>The documentary is available on Netflix. I generally dislike documentaries and avoid them. This one was very well done though. The arguments that absent any constraints from bureaucracy present elsewhere comics acted as a means for communicating social reform were well laid out.<br />
<br />
It's interesting in another way how it is another instance of the perception of rules and conventions being necessary and imposed upon a group inorganically ultimately subtracts away some to all of the value the group created before gatekeepers felt compelled to wet their own beak, something that is continually repeated elsewhere in organizations.<br />
<br />
While I haven't read any erotic comics, the interviews with the domain masters were interesting, how diverse their styles and motivations were, their perceptions of their own works etc.<br />
<br />
The entire documentary is about an hour long.</div>

