			<pubDate>Sat, 04 Jun 2016 17:53:36 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2016/06/04/sports/muhammad-ali-quotes.html?hp&action=click&pgtype=Homepage&clickSource=story-heading&module=a-lede-package-region&region=top-news&WT.nav=top-news&_r=0 
 
I was never a huge boxing fan, but I can watch Muhammad Ali fights one after another for an...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2016/06/04/sports/muhammad-ali-quotes.html?hp&amp;action=click&amp;pgtype=Homepage&amp;clickSource=story-heading&amp;module=a-lede-package-region&amp;region=top-news&amp;WT.nav=top-news&amp;_r=0" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2...=top-news&amp;_r=0</a><br />
<br />
I was never a huge boxing fan, but I can watch Muhammad Ali fights one after another for an indefinite amount of time.<br />
<br />
(The only other boxing match I enjoy re-watching is Tyson vs. Buster Douglas.)<br />
<br />
I must have about six different DVD's about Ali's life and times.  I think one just focuses on the &quot;Rumble in the Jungle.&quot;  Another focuses on all his early fights before the ban.  -Several complete lifetime compilations and the one with Will Smith.  I'll be watching them all again today I think.<br />
<br />
No one will ever convince me there was ever a greater boxer than Muhammad Ali.<br />
<br />
His victory over Foreman in Zaire, at his age at the time, was the epitome of EPIC.  There is nothing more epic than that victory.<br />
<br />
And if you watch his early fights before the ban, holy fuck there was never anything like him.  Lightning fast, truly, and powerful.  Many of those fights show him literally TOYING with his opponents.  -Dancing around, dodging every punch, doing big wind-ups before his punches, etc.  He was in a league of his own.<br />
<br />
A very sorrowful loss for our generation.<br />
<br />
:(<br />
